.TH "pcpu_mem_zalloc" 9 "pcpu_mem_zalloc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pcpu_mem_zalloc \- allocate memory
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void *" pcpu_mem_zalloc
.BI "(size_t size "  ","
.BI "gfp_t gfp "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "size" 12
bytes to allocate
.IP "gfp" 12
allocation flags
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocate \fIsize\fP bytes.  If \fIsize\fP is smaller than PAGE_SIZE,
\fBkzalloc\fP is used; otherwise, the equivalent of \fBvzalloc\fP is used.
This is to facilitate passing through whitelisted flags.  The
returned memory is always zeroed.
.SH "RETURN"
Pointer to the allocated area on success, NULL on failure.
